Title: Dabur
Description: Dabur Ltd is an Indian multinational consumer goods company, founded by S. K. Burman and headquartered in Ghaziabad.[4] It manufactures Ayurvedic medicine and natural consumer products,[5] and is one of the largest fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG) companies in India.[6] Dabur derives around 60% of its revenue from the consumer care business, 11% from the food business and remaining from the international business unit

Title: Zandu
Description: Zandu is a 110-year-old Ayurvedic company that carefully follows the legacy of ancient Ayurvedic scriptures such as Sushrutha Samhita and Charaka Samhita.
